# ByteRover CLI — API provider keys (copy to .env.brv.local; gitignored).
# Used by: npm run setup-brv-provider, scripts/start-brv-mcp.sh
#
# Set ONE provider key (priority if multiple: OpenRouter > Anthropic > OpenAI > Google):
#
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...
#
# Optional overrides:
# BRV_PROVIDER=openrouter   # force provider id (openrouter|anthropic|openai|google|byterover)
# BRV_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5   # Anthropic default in setup-brv-api-provider.sh
# BRV_OAUTH=1               # with BRV_PROVIDER=byterover only
#
# OAuth (no key in file — run in terminal):
#   brv providers connect openai --oauth
#   brv providers connect byterover --oauth
#
# Local Ollama is NOT recommended for brv curate (memory/tool-call constraints).
